# 🌐 AWS S3 Portfolio Website with HTTPS & IAM Security

## 📌 Project Overview
This project demonstrates the deployment and securing of my personal portfolio website using AWS. The website is hosted on **Amazon S3** and delivered via **CloudFront**. I enhanced its security by enabling **HTTPS** and configuring **IAM permissions**, following AWS best practices.

This is part of my journey toward becoming an **AWS Community Builder**, learning **Cloud, DevOps, and AI** concepts.

---

## 🛠️ Services Used
- Amazon S3 (Static Website Hosting)  
- Amazon CloudFront (Content Delivery Network)  
- AWS IAM (Identity and Access Management)  

---

## ⚙️ What I Implemented
- Hosted the portfolio website on S3  
- Configured CloudFront for fast global delivery  
- Enabled HTTPS for secure access  
- Set up IAM permissions to control access  
- Learned and applied AWS Cloud Practitioner concepts:
  - Scalability
  - Elasticity
  - Amazon SQS (Simple Queue Service)
  - Amazon SNS (Simple Notification Service)

